# OBSTRUCTION module

## Description
The OBSTRUCTIONS module have been implemented to take account modifications of 
hydrodynamics induced by differents kinds of obstructions. 
This is a generic module adapted to various types of natural and anthropogenic 
obstructions that can be found in coastal ecosystems (i.e. rigid/flexible, 
submerged/emergent, upward/downward/3D).

## Authors
- F. Ganthy (IFREMER) — original development (MARS model)
- S. Le Gac (IFREMER) — adaptation to standalone module in CROCO, 2023

## Features
- Rigid and flexible obstructions (upward, downward, 3D)
- Bending parameterization (exponential or Abdelrhman 2007 method)
- Vertical distribution of obstruction density
- Horizontal coverage correction (fracxy)

## Reference
Florian Ganthy, Romaric Verney, Arnaud Le Pevedic, and Franck Dumas. 
Modelling water flow in presence of various obstructions: description and 
validation of a generic module for 2- and 3-dimensional simulations. 
Continental Shelf Research, 295:105580, 2025. 
URL: https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0278434325001803, 
doi:https://doi.org/10.1016/j.csr.2025.105580.

